8 §9031. Veterans Service Grant Board; disbursement of funds
9 A. The Veterans Service Grant Board, hereafter referred to as the "veterans
10 board", is hereby created to be solely responsible for the disbursement of the funds
11 in the Veterans Service Grant Fund to programs or entities with the purpose of
12 bettering the lives of veterans in this state. Veterans board members shall serve
13 without compensation and shall not require confirmation by the Senate.
14 B. The secretary of the Department of Veterans Affairs shall serve as
15 chairman until the first meeting of the veterans board, at which time the veterans
16 board shall elect a chairman and vice chairman. The chairman and vice chairman
17 shall be elected annually.
18 C. The veterans board shall meet annually in person to review submitted
19 grant applications and disburse grant funds to selected applicants.
