Abstract: Creates the Veterans Service Grant Board and provides for allocation and
distribution of lottery proceeds for the benefit of La. veterans.
Proposed law (R.S. 47:9031) creates the Veterans Service Grant Bd. and provides for
composition, recordkeeping, meeting requirements, and other matters relative to board
functions.
Proposed law requires the Veterans Service Grant Bd. to disburse funds through one-time
grants. Further provides certain criteria for grant applicants.
Proposed law (R.S. 47:9032) provides for the Veterans Service Grant Fund (Fund) and
requires the treasurer to deposit $500,000, pursuant to the Constitution of La., into the Fund.
Further requires the treasurer to invest proceeds in the same manner as monies in the state
general fund.
Proposed law requires unused principal funds at the end of each year to be deposited in and
credited to the minimum foundation program. Further requires interest earned on
investments to remain in the Fund.
(Adds R.S. 47:9031 and 9032)
